analysis: The agent incorrectly added an unsupported "emotion_depth" parameter to the poetry_theme_emotion_analyzer call, resulting in a function call signature mismatch with the expected tool input and causing evaluation failure.

The agent included an unsupported "safety_checks" field under "locking_mechanism" in its function call, thus failing to match the required schema for adjust_seat_safety, which only accepts "status" for locking_mechanism.
The agent included an unsupported parameter "printTime" in the function arguments, causing its function call to not match the expected schema and resulting in a failure to invoke the tool correctly.

The agent included unnecessary "details" about protocol steps in the DeviceConnection_authenticateBluetooth function's arguments, resulting in a parameter structure mismatch and failure to correctly call the function as specified by the tool's expected input schema.

The agent output "pop" in lowercase for the genre parameter, while the expected function call required "Pop" with an uppercase "P"; the parameter value did not match the expected case-sensitive format.

The agent incorrectly included a trailing period in the "content" argument, causing a mismatch with the expected function call, which did not include the period. This led to the evaluator not recognizing the function call as correct.

The agent incorrectly added an "eventTypes" argument not specified in the available tool's schema, resulting in a function call signature mismatch and failure to invoke the correct tool. Only "caseId" and "timeRange" were expected.

The agent included an extra unexpected "features" field (as an empty list) in the "simulation_parameters" argument, resulting in a function call that did not exactly match the expected schema and thus caused a mismatch.

The agent incorrectly included the "feedbackMode": "textual" parameter in the correctionPreferences object, which was not part of the expected function signature. This extraneous parameter caused the function calls to not match the expected format.

The agent used the correct function but omitted leading zeros in the year field ("100-08-01" instead of "0100-08-01"), causing its calls not to match the expected parameters. This formatting error in the date string led to evaluation failure.

The agent only made a single function call for the first date range and failed to issue a second function call for the July 10-12 period, thus not checking both requested time periods as the task required.

The agent added an unsupported "dataOptions" parameter with subfields ("includeHumidity" and "updateFrequency") to the function call, causing a mismatch with the expected function signature, which only required location and time parameters.
